descriptionHtml:
The Association to Support the Rights of the Palestinian People, known as the International Commission to Support the Palestinian People, is a non-profit civil rights organization, established in 2015 and registered under No. 8523 based on the Palestinian NGOs and Organizations Law. No. 01 of 2000. The international body works to protect human rights and the rights of the Palestinian people.
The Commission embodies its vision in the struggle for a free and democratic Palestinian society in which the rule of law and human rights are respected.
The Commission seeks to protect human rights in Palestine, raise awareness and culture of national and human rights among Palestinians, and mobilize international support and solidarity with the rights of the Palestinian people, using strategies, tactics, and tools for monitoring, documentation, and national and international protection of human rights.
descriptionShort: This app for the International Commission to support Palestinian Peoples Rights.
